reason.tex:
%text First, $\because$ = because.
Now, a function is increasing \underline\text{in an interval} if \[ \frac{df}{d\theta} \geq 0\] \underline\text{in that interval}.
So, we must first find $\frac{df}{d\theta}$. % \begin{align} f(\theta) &= \frac{4\sin\theta}{(\cos\theta + 2)} -\theta \\ \therefore\frac{df}{d\theta} &= 4\underbrace{\left[ \frac{(\cos\theta + 2)\cdot\cos\theta + \sin^2\theta}{(\cos\theta+2)^2}\right]}_{\text{Quotient Rule}}-1\\ &= 4\left[ \frac{\overbrace{\cos^2\theta+\sin^2\theta}^{=1} + 2\cos\theta}{(\cos\theta + 2)^2}\right] - 1\\ &= \frac{4\cdot(1+2\cos\theta) - (\cos\theta+2)^2}{(\cos\theta+2)^2}\\ &= \frac{\cos\theta\cdot(4-\cos\theta)}{(\cos\theta + 2)^2}\geq 0 \text{ for }\theta\in\left[ 0,\frac\pi{2}\right]\\ &(\because \cos\theta, (4-\cos\theta)\text{ and }(\cos\theta+2)^2\geq 0) \end{align}
